short_description: Weeks after the nationwide COVID-19 lockdown, seven migrant labourers, on the verge of starvation, decided to go to their village just like millions of others.
The Dutch village of Ruinerwold becomes world news when a hidden farm is discovered, where a family lived secretly and unregistered for years. The four oldest children tell their story.
